{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Battle_Lost",
  "title": "A Battle Lost",
  "summary": "Within the cold marble halls of the Imperial Embassy, the bounty hunter Taggor delivers the mercenary Normack Gastrov to the Imperial Vice Director Joir, who has summoned him over events at Tatooine and a shooting in Plaxton square. Leading Normack through the corridor into his austere office under armed guard, Joir demands to know what was taken from the Empire and presses him about a man named Lorn Rhys. Normack, blunt and contemptuous, refuses to be intimidated and steers the conversation like a chess game, recognizing that the information he holds is valuable enough that Joir will not simply kill or surrender him. The two engage in a tense battle of wits that Taggor silently judges an even match, until Normack names his price: immunity from prosecution, safe transport off-world, and five thousand credits. Joir agrees, handing over a credit chip to be activated upon receipt of useful intelligence, then fires off a rapid string of questions about who attacked the ship, who financed it, and where Lorn is now.",
